prometheus_expr.description:
Required PromQL expression which the derived metric executes. Should
include all configured variables.

variables.description:
Optional variables which may be used in the derived metric as label
selectors.

labels.description:
Labels which must match in the derived metric usage for the selector to
match.

name.description: Required name of the variable.

default_prometheus_selector.description:
Required PromQL label selector which must match the given variable name.
If the variable is not specified in the derived metric usage, then this
default selector is used.

rate_limit_threshold.description:
Percentage of the licensed limit reached in order to activate the drop
rule, between 0 and 100.

activated_drop_duration_secs.description:
Once activated, activated_drop_duration_secs defines how long the drop
rule stays activated before rechecking against the rate_limit_threshold.

target_drop_value.description: The target datapoint value at which to drop metrics.

project_id.description: Project ID that has access to the metric data.

prefixes.description: List of Gcp metric prefixes to ingest.

name.description:
Required name of the label whose value should be replaced. Only
`__gX__` labels are allowed (aka positional Graphite labels).

new_value.description: Required new value of the replaced label.

GroupByGroupByKey.description: GroupByKey describes a key to group by.

named_key.description: For named KeyTypes (e.g. span tags), the name of the key to group by.

GroupByKeyGroupByKeyType.description:
- SERVICE: Group by service.
 - OPERATION: Group by operation.
 - TAG: Group by span tag.

insecure_skip_verify.description: Disables validation of the server certificate.

source_label.description: The actual label ingested on the time series

value_mappings.description: These value mappings apply to just the name mapping they belong to.

source_value_globs.description: Defines the source label values that should be mapped into the given target_value.

target_value.description:
The value that source_value_globs are mapped into.
For example, given this mapping:
```yaml
value_mappings:
 - source_value_globs:
     - Cat
     - CAT
   target_value: cat
```
This indicates that the target value `cat` maps to the source label's values `Cat` and `CAT`.

interval.description:
Interval between aggregated data points, equivalent to the resolution
field in storage policy. If set, then the storage_policy field can't be
set.

drop_timestamp.description: Deprecated: This field is no longer supported.

value_mappings.description:
These value mappings apply to the whole mapping label.
If there's no name_mappings, these value mappings apply to the label that exists on the metric.

value.description: The value to compare to the metric value using the op operation.

sustain_secs.description: Time op operation must evaluate to true for the condition to evaluate to true.

resolve_sustain_secs.description: Time op operation must evaluate as false for an active alert, before that alert resolves.

timezone.description: The timezone of the time ranges.

MonitorSeriesConditions.description: Conditions evaluated against each queried series to determine the severity of each series.

overrides.description:
Optional list of overrides to use for series having matching labels.
Each override defines labels that potentially match a series' labels.
If one or more overrides match a series, the severity conditions of the first matching
override are used instead of the defaults.

Cannot be used if graphite_query is set.

label_matchers.description:
Set of matchers on a series' labels.
If all labels match then the conditions defined in this override are used.

MonitorSignalGrouping.description: SignalGrouping defines how the set of series from the query are split into signals.

label_names.description:
Set of labels names used to split series into signals.
Each unique combination of labels will result in its own signal.
For example, if label_names is ["service", "code"] then all series including labels {service="foo",code="404"}
will be grouped together in the same signal.

Cannot be used if graphite_query is set.

signal_per_series.description:
If this is true, each series will have its own signal.
If this is true then label_names cannot be set.

overrides.description:
Optional list of overrides to use for alerts having matching labels.
Each override defines labels that potentially match an alert's labels.
If one or more overrides match an alert, the notifiers of the first matching
override are used instead of the defaults.

alert_label_matchers.description:
Set of matchers on an alert's labels.
If all labels match then the override notifiers apply.

to.description: Required email address to send notifications to.

html.description: Optional HTML body of the email.

text.description: Optional text body of the email.

bearer_token.description: Bearer token authentication. Cannot be set if basic_auth is set.

proxy_url.description:
Optional proxy URL.
DEPRECATED: Custom proxies are unsupported.

api_url.description:
Required OpsGenie API URL to send requests to, e.g.
"https://api.opsgenie.com/".

source.description: A backlink to the sender of the notification.

details.description:
A set of arbitrary key/value pairs that provide further detail about the
alert.

responders.description: List of responders responsible for notifications.

tags.description: Comma separated list of tags attached to the notifications.

priority.description: Priority level of alert. Possible values are P1, P2, P3, P4, and P5.

url.description: The Pagerduty URL to send API requests to.

client.description: Client identification of the notification sender.

client_url.description: A backlink to the sender of the notification.

severity.description:
Severity of the incident.
Valid values are 'critical', 'error', 'warning', 'info', or blank

component.description: The part or component of the affected system which is broken.

group.description: A cluster or grouping of services.

details.description:
Set of arbitrary key/value pairs which provide further detail about the
incident.

images.description: Images to attach to the incident.

links.description: Links to attach to the incident.

service_key.description:
The PagerDuty integration key (when using PagerDuty integration type
"Prometheus"). Cannot be set if routing_key is set.

routing_key.description:
The PagerDuty integration key (when using PagerDuty integration type
"Events API v2"). Cannot be set if service_key is set.

channel.description: The channel to send notifications to.

username.description: The user to send notifications to.

message_type.description: Describes the behavior of the alert (CRITICAL, WARNING, INFO).

state_message.description: Long explanation of the alerted problem.

monitoring_tool.description: The monitoring tool the state message is from.

url.description: Required webhook URL (will be called as a POST request).

id.description: ID of the responder. Cannot be set if name or username are set.

name.description: Name of the responder. Cannot be set if id or username are set.

username.description: Username of the responder. Cannot be set if id or name are set.

operation.description: The operation to which this specific strategy should apply.

percent_of_license.description:
Percentage of the license to allocate to this pool. Must be between 0
and 100 inclusive. The percent_of_license values across all pools
(including the default pool) must add up to exactly 100.

name.description: Required name of the pool. Must be unique.

filters.description:
Required filters which define which metrics map to this pool, where any
metric which matches at least one filter will map to the pool.

high_priority_filters.description:
Required filters which define which metrics are high priority, where any
metric which matches at least one filter is considered high priority.
High priority metrics are dropped last when the license limit is exceeded.

low_priority_filters.description:
Required filters which define which metrics are low priority, where any
metric which matches at least one filter is considered low priority. Low
priority metrics are dropped first when the license limit is exceeded.

replace.description:
Required list of labels to replace. Useful for discarding
high-cardinality values while still preserving the original positions of
the Graphite metric.

RollupRuleLabelReplace.description:
Must keep this around for backwards compatibility because terraform will
still send this key w/ a null value.

RollupRuleMetricType.description:
- CUMULATIVE_COUNTER: Alias of COUNTER.
 - DELTA_COUNTER: Alias of DELTA.

notifier_slugs.description: Slugs of notifiers that will receive the alerts.

repeat_interval_secs.description: Frequency at which to resend alerts.

start_hh_mm.description: Start time in the in format "<hour>:<minute>", e.g. "15:30".

end_hh_mm.description: End time in the in format "<hour>:<minute>", e.g. "15:30".

ranges.description:
The time ranges that the monitor is active on this day. Required if
active is set to ONLY_DURING_RANGES, else must be empty.

conditions.description:
List of conditions to evaluate against a series.
Only one condition -- not all -- needs to match in order to assign a severity to a signal.

labels.description:
Optional labels which further restricts the service account to only read
or write metrics with the given label names and values.

match all muting rule matchers to be silenced.
This value cannot be updated. Updates must specify the original value.

This value cannot be updated. Updates must specify the original value.

ends_at.description: Timestamp of when the muting rule stops being active.

name.description: name always matches against an exact label name.

team_slug is not set.

bucket_slug is not set.

updated_at.description: Timestamp of when the Notifier was last updated. Cannot be set by clients.

notifications. Cannot set if another integration is set.

metric_name.description:
The name of the time series to use for output, which must be a valid
metric name.

prometheus_expr.description:
The PromQL expression to evaluate at the time of each evaluation cycle.
The result is recorded as a new time series with its metric name
defined by the metric_name (or name) field.

execution_group.description:
Optional execution_group in which this rule is to be evaluated.
At least one of bucket_slug and execution_group must be set. If both are set, then they are expected to match.

add.description: Labels to add or overwrite before storing the result.

created_at.description: Timestamp of when the ResourcePools was created. Cannot be set by clients.

updated_at.description: Timestamp of when the ResourcePools was last updated. Cannot be set by clients.

pools.description: Optional pools. Cannot set more than 20 pools.

slug.description: Unique identifier of the RollupRule. If slug is not provided, one will be generated based of the name field. Cannot be modified after the RollupRule is created.

name.description: Required name of the RollupRule. May be modified after the RollupRule is created.

created_at.description: Timestamp of when the RollupRule was created. Cannot be set by clients.

updated_at.description: Timestamp of when the RollupRule was last updated. Cannot be set by clients.

bucket_slug.description: Required slug of the bucket the RollupRule belongs to.

filters.description: Filters that determine to which metrics to apply the rule.

metric_name.description: Name of the new metric created as a result of the rollup.

interval.description:
Interval between aggregated data points, equivalent to the resolution
field in storage policy. If set, then the storage_policy field can't be
set.

expansive_match.description:
Enables expansive label matching behavior for the provided filters and
label_policy.keep or graphite_label_policy.replace (if set). By default
(expansive_match=false), a series matches and aggregates only if each label
defined by filters and label_policy.keep or graphite_label_policy.replace
(respectively) exist in said series. Setting expansive_match=true removes
this restriction.

add_metric_type_label.description: Defines whether to add a `__rollup_type__` label in the new metric.

drop_raw.description: Defines whether to automatically generate drop rules for this rollup.

 entities implement the same label semantics.

discard field must be empty.

discard.description:
Labels that should be discarded in the output metric. If set, then the
keep field must be empty.

resolution.description: Required resolution of the aggregated metrics.

retention.description: Required retention of the aggregated metrics.

Slug of the notification policy used by default for monitors in this service collection.
This is optional if the collection does not contain monitors or all of its monitors explicitly reference a policy.
This does not override the policy used when a monitor explicitly references a policy.

clients.

token is only set once by the server in the CreateServiceAccount response.
ReadServiceAccount will always return an empty token. Therefore, when
creating a service account, clients are responsible for securely storing
the response token on their end, as they will not be able to read it
again.

email.description:
email is the generated email address of the service account. Cannot be set
by clients.

If set, grants the service account access to all Chronosphere APIs
(including resource configuration and metric data) within the access
controls defined by the service account's team membership.

Exactly one of unrestricted or metrics_restriction must be set.

configv1TraceBehaviorConfig.description:
TraceBehaviorConfig is a singleton configuration object that specifies the
configuration for trace behaviors.

created_at.description: Timestamp of when the TraceBehaviorConfig was created. Cannot be set by clients.

updated_at.description: Timestamp of when the TraceBehaviorConfig was last updated. Cannot be set by clients.

main_behavior_assignments.description:
List of assignments for the main behavior. The referenced datasets are datasets 
to be enrolled in behaviors. The referenced behaviors are the active behaviors
for the dataset when there is no override in place. 
* Only one main behavior can be assigned to a dataset.
* Only one referenced `TraceBehavior` with `type` field set to `TYPE_BASELINE` can
be set, which must match the slug referenced by `baseline_behavior_slug`.

override_behavior_assignments.description:
List of assignments for the override behavior. OverrideBehaviorAssignments are used to
specify the active behavior for a dataset over a specific time range.
* Only one override behavior can be assigned to a dataset.
* Only one referenced `TraceBehavior` with `type` field set to `TYPE_BASELINE` can
be set, which must match the slug referenced by `baseline_behavior_slug`, and any
baseline behavior referenced in `main_behavior_assignments`.

dataset_priorities.description:
List of dataset priorities. This list specifies the order in which datasets
are considered when determining the behavior to follow for a trace. Dataset
priorities are used to break ties when a trace matches more than one dataset
with an active behavior.
* Each entry in this list must refer to the slug of an existing dataset.
* The order of the list is the order in which the datasets are considered.
* The list must contain all datasets referenced in either main_behavior_assignments
  and override_behavior_assignments.
* The list may contain datasets that are not referenced in either of the above.

baseline_behavior_slug.description:
The baseline behavior to use for behavior assignments and base head sampling rates. Must reference a
TraceBehavior entity with type: TYPE_BASELINE.

updated_at.description: Timestamp of when the TraceMetricsRule was last updated. Cannot be set by clients.

metric_labels.description: Labels to apply to the generated trace metrics.

histogram_buckets_secs.description: Histogram bucket values, in seconds, for generated duration metrics.

group_by.description: Add labels to the resultant metrics based on these specified GroupBy messages.

configv1TraceMetricsRuleGroupBy.description: GroupBy contains fields required to group the resultant metrics of a TraceMetricsRule by a specific key.

label.description: The label to use in the resultant metrics.

span.description:
Each SpanFilter object represents all conditions that need to be true on
the same span for the span to be considered matching the SpanFilter. If
`span_count` is used, the number of spans within the trace that match the
SpanFilter needs to be within [min, max]. Multiple SpanFilters can be used,
and each can be satisfied by any number of spans within the trace.

configv1TraceTailSamplingRule.description: Contains configuration for one tail sampling rule.

sample_rate.description: A fraction of traces to keep, which should be a number between 0 and 1, inclusive

name.description: A human-readable name of the rule, which summarizes what it's for

system_name.description: Value used as the metric label value for metrics emitted relating to this rule.

created_at.description: When the rule was created (novel system_name)

updated_at.description: When the rule was updated (existing system_name)

configv1TraceTailSamplingRules.description: Root object containing all tail sampling rules (for a tenant).

created_at.description: Set in API responses.

updated_at.description: Set in API responses.

rules.description:
Optional. A list of rules, evaluated in order until a match is found,
and the sample rate applied, or else the default sample rate is applied.
